    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Paying Is Half the Fun</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gene Damm letter comments on William Grimes's July 12 article on new Manhattan restaurant operated by Alain Ducasse (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>William Grimes's article was a gas. The subtext is that fine dining can be a classic luxury item, by which I mean there is considerable psychic satisfaction in paying through the nose. People who snag a reservation at Ducasse anticipate high prices. It's an essential aspect of the dining experience. You can brag about it afterward.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>William Grimes's article was a gas. The subtext is that fine dining can be a classic luxury item, by which I mean there is considerable psychic satisfaction in paying through the nose. People who snag a reservation at Ducasse anticipate high prices. It's an essential aspect of the dining experience. You can brag about it afterward.</p>
        <p>Ducasse may be different in degree, but not in kind from other Manhattan restaurateurs. As long as the market is up, he's a marketing genius!</p>
        <p>GENE DAMM  Albany</p>
      </block>
